description: From Medieval Latin prōiectilis (“projectile”), from Latin prōiectus, perfect passive participle of prōiciō (“throw forth; extend; expel”).

examples: a projectile force; a projectile weapon

entries.meaning: Caused or imparted by impulse or projection; impelled forward.
examples: A free and strong Projectile Motion of the Blood must occasion a florid Appearance upon the Skin in such Constitutions

entries.meaning: An object intended to be or having been fired from a weapon.
(physics) Any object propelled or thrown through space by the application of a force, such as strong wind.
